  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-01 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed; 13 credibility factors assessed. A central hemolysis-threshold claim is registered and appears well-supported by accompanying validation results; however the claim node itself carries no prov:wasDerivedFrom link to any Evidence node, constituting an epistemic orphan under W-EP-01.",
